Use `packaging.version.Version` instead.

Merge pull request #34 from Cangjians/docker

Docker-based CI

resolves #31.
ci: Simplify installing in the right place on Debian-like systems

ci: Move some stuff around

With this, the Travis config file is almost identical to the libcangjie
one.

ci: Use the libcangjie image as a base

This does much the same as what we did for libcangjie already:

1. pull the base image
2. build and install pycangjie in it
3. run the tests

The only difference is that the base image is the libcangjie one in this
case, not the build-essential one any more.

We reuse the same parametrization trick, which requires us to upgrade
Docker.

ci: We don't need to run both check and distcheck

The latter already runs the former.

ci: Remove the unnecessary ENTRYPOINT and CMD

There's no need to define an instruction to its default value.

In addition we already specify the command to run in the .travis.yml
file for the CI.
ci: Use the latest images from our Docker Hub organization

ci: Remove the local build

We now have these fancy Docker images to test libcangjie on modern
operating systems, so let's get rid of the ancient stuff provided by
Travis.

ci: Don't run on all branches, just on master

Travis will run the CI on pull requests no matter what.

However, without this setting it will **also** run the CI on every
branch.

Since pull requests are based on branches, Travis runs the CI twice for
pull requests... unless we set this.
Travis: Add opensuse-leap as test target
Multi OS dockerfile and test

travis: Test docker build

Test Dockerfile build in travis.

Basic docker setup

Added Dockerfile and .dockerignore for building the docker image
"cangjians/pycangjie" from "cangjians/libcangjie".

This image is an essential ground for testing ibus-cangjie and / or
other software based upon libcangjie in docker environment.
